        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 5:25PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 524 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers and thunderstorms
with gusty winds along a line extending from 8 miles southeast of
Whitehall to 11 miles southwest of Manhattan to 11 miles southwest
of Bozeman. Movement was north at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Bozeman, Belgrade, Three Forks, Manhattan, Whitehall, Toston,
Harrison, Bozeman Hot Springs, Gallatin Gateway, Missouri Headwaters
State Park, Cardwell, Logan, Radersburg, Lewis And Clark Caverns
State Park, Maudlow, Four Corners, Amsterdam, Trident, Church Hill,
and Willow Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
